parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the transmission makes a loud "clunking" or "popping" noise
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the check engine light comes on
the O/D light blinks or flashes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to not start or crank, leading to inconvenience and potentially dangerous situations, such as the steering column smoking and almost catching on fire.
symptoms: The vehicle is difficult to start or crank
the vehicle only makes a clicking sound when trying to start
the steering column smokes or catches on fire while trying to start the vehicle
